  <title>bson_context_new()</title>

  <section id="synopsis">
    <title>Synopsis</title>
    <synopsis><code mime="text/x-csrc"><![CDATA[bson_context_t *
bson_context_new (bson_context_flags_t flags);
]]></code></synopsis>
  </section>

  <section id="parameters">
    <title>Parameters</title>
    <table>
      <tr><td><p><code>flags</code></p></td><td><p>A <code xref="bson_context_t">bson_context_flags_t</code>.</p></td></tr>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section id="description">
    <title>Description</title>
    <p>Creates a new <code xref="bson_context_t">bson_context_t</code>. This is rarely needed as <code xref="bson_context_get_default">bson_context_get_default()</code> serves most use-cases.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="return">
    <title>Returns</title>
    <p>A newly allocated <code xref="bson_context_t">bson_context_t</code> that should be freed with <code xref="bson_context_destroy">bson_context_destroy</code>.</p>
  </section>
